Installation:
-------------

Prerequisites: 

- Python 2.6 or higher: 
      http://www.python.org/

- NumPy:
      http://numpy.scipy.org/

- ScientificPython 2.8 or higher:
      http://dirac.cnrs-orleans.fr/ScientificPython/

- FFTW3:
      http://www.fftw.org/

- GSL:
      http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/

CDTK will use Numeric or NumPy depending on how ScientificPython has been
configured.

The MTZ file reader requires the CCP4 library,

    http://www.ccp4.ac.uk/main.html

whose location should be indicated by the environment variable 'CCP4'.

Alternatively, the freely distributable GPP4 library,

     http://launchpad.net/gpp4

can be used, whose location should be indicated by the environment
variable 'GPP4'. If neither CCP4 nor GPP4 is defined, the MTZ file
reader will not be installed.



Once the prerequisites are available, installation of CDTK is as simple as

    python setup.py build
    python setup.py install

(the second command requires root privileges on many installations).
